20^2 = a^2 + x^2
13^2 = a^2 + (21 -x)^2
a^2 = \color{blue}{\bf 20^2 - x^2 = 13^2 - (21-x)^2 }
400 - x^2 = 169 - (441 - 42x + x^2) = -272 + 42x - x^2
672 = 42x \iff x = 16.
x = 16 \implies a = \sqrt{400 - x^2} = \sqrt{400 - 256} = 12
